00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:22,743
you're really setting the technical direction for the next seven to ten years of game development.

225
00:16:22,743 --> 00:16:28,045
So we really design the hardware in such a way that we're thinking about where games can be going.

226
00:16:28,725 --> 00:16:38,188
Right now, a lot of the positive press and the feedback we're getting from developers is really on the massive improvements in load times.

227
00:16:38,188 --> 00:16:46,030
But that's, in many cases, just really leveraging the raw hardware capabilities that the SSD drive brings to bear.

228
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:49,791
When you think about what we've actually done with the Xbox Velocity architecture,

229
00:16:50,231 --> 00:16:54,894
It was a radical rethink of how game streaming can and should work,

230
00:16:54,894 --> 00:16:58,516
with an eye towards these larger, more dynamic living worlds,

231
00:16:58,516 --> 00:17:04,359
where basically there's entire classes of assets that you don't even need to load into memory anymore,

232
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:10,262
because we have that ultra-fast I.O. between the processor and the I.O. subsystem.

233
00:17:10,262 --> 00:17:13,684
You also think about things like, as a developer,

234
00:17:13,684 --> 00:17:18,046
developers always would love more memory, more GPU, more CPU horsepower.

235
00:17:19,427 --> 00:17:21,990
A huge part for us is the efficiency.

236
00:17:21,990 --> 00:17:26,295
So, you know, for us it's critically important that we have consistent, sustained clocks

237
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:30,060
so developers don't have to worry about variable performance.

238
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:33,925
Because that makes it harder to optimize your game, you know, whether you're in intense

239
00:17:33,925 --> 00:17:37,549
firefight or you're in just kind of another part of the world.

240
00:17:38,107 --> 00:17:41,709
We also look at things like variable rate shading, like I mentioned before.

241
00:17:41,709 --> 00:17:47,672
It's really about, you know, obviously we're really proud of the raw GPU performance that we have,

242
00:17:47,672 --> 00:17:52,615
but it's how can we let developers be even more efficient in how they use that power.

243
00:17:52,615 --> 00:17:57,817
So with something like variable rate shading, if something's in shadow or it's, you know,

244
00:17:57,817 --> 00:18:03,581
got motion blur or whatnot, you probably don't need that same level of precision for that area of the

245
00:18:03,581 --> 00:18:04,021
frame.

246
00:18:04,421 --> 00:18:08,643
but now I can take that extra power that I'm not applying to that area of the frame

247
00:18:08,643 --> 00:18:13,345
and putting it in my hero character or objects that are closer to the camera.

248
00:18:13,345 --> 00:18:20,148
So it really allows us to deliver performance well beyond the raw hardware specs themselves.

249
00:18:20,148 --> 00:18:24,350
And I think you'll see, you know, over the course of the generation, you'll really see

250
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:29,272
both us and developers really understanding how to take full advantage of all these capabilities

251
00:18:29,272 --> 00:18:33,494
to really deliver transformative game experiences unlike anything you've seen before.

252
00:18:34,044 --> 00:18:40,169
So maybe fewer elevators and fewer long hallways and narrow paths.

