273
00:20:11,258 --> 00:20:13,540
they have access to the full I.O. performance.

274
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:19,986
And what that allows us to do is it allows us to actually run the games better than they've ever been run before,

275
00:20:19,986 --> 00:20:24,029
oftentimes even further than the original hardware that they were originally designed for.

276
00:20:24,614 --> 00:20:27,797
So one of the critical things that's important to us though,

277
00:20:27,797 --> 00:20:32,861
is that we never violate that artistic intent of that original creator.

278
00:20:32,861 --> 00:20:35,824
So, you know, we're never going to run a game at, say, you know,

279
00:20:35,824 --> 00:20:38,446
ultra high frame rates and then, you know,

